	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: New game - Driar</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The levels, chr animations, title screen, are completely uncompressed. I don't know how MUSE stores its data, or how optimized its engine is for space. There's somewhere around another 20KiB or so that are obviously just padding still. Chances are good that the full game could be stuffed into 32kiB + CHR RAM.<br />Counted by hexdump's output, there are â‰ˆ30000 bytes of sequences of 16 bytes that are an exact repetition of the previous 16.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
